    "updated_at": "2016-05-30T22:10:09Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Makes sense, :+1: \n\n@RoosterDragon: the check in the extension method tests the actor's `CurrentActivity`. With both `MoveAdjacentTo` and `AttackMove`, the `Move` activities are inner activities that never get promoted to be the `CurrentActivity`. The check in the `Tick` method however sets the `IsMoving` flag only when _its_ inner activity returns a `Move`-related activity. Since this will also happen when the `Move` is actually an inner activity itself, it doesn't need to check for `MoveAdjacentTo` or `AttackMove`, it already works implicitly.\n"
  },
